        "Description/Abstract": "This article draws tax planning lessons from AIG Insurance Management Services, Inc. v. Vermont Department of Taxes.  In AIG, the Supreme Court of Vermont found a corporate group\u2019s ski resort was not part of its unitary insurance business.   Although the taxpayer won in AIG, the case was a close one.  In an age of proliferating combined reporting laws, AIG serves as a reminder to corporations to carefully plan and consistently report the scope of their unitary businesses\u2014especially when dealing with diverse business lines.   ",
